Success at work is a primary goal. No one wants to fail. There are many ways to achieve success such as through intense competition or utilizing cooperation. Some might argue that competition is the best way to achieve success but in reality, that isn't the case. Cooperation is powerful and drives people more than competition.\n       While competition can drive people to work since they want to win, it creates a culture of secrecy and rivalry. It doesn't foster idea-sharing. It might work for short-term success but it will not sustain long-term success. Cooperation creates a culture of camaraderie. It fosters and nurtures idea-sharing. The term \"two heads are better than one\" is true for a reason. For this reason, cooperation will allow people to achieve more success.
